    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yep in your case it's a bit different, we try by default in the template to show the numbers in the user locale (1,000 or 1 000 or 1.000). Thus when modifying it to be \"100k\", it becomes a string, no more a number (and results in NaN Not A Number in JS)\n",
